    <main>
      <section class="container">
        <h2 class="subheading">COVID-19 Status</h2>

        <h3 class="subheading date">28/06/20</h3>

        <p>
          The government are now permitting weddings to proceed with a maximum
          guest limit of 30 guests, depending on the venue's ability to
          accommodate guests whilst maintaining social distancing. As such, we
          are currently only permitted 16 guests at our chosen venue. This means
          that only our immediate family members will be able to attend the
          wedding ceremony. For the time being, we regretfully must ask that
          guests who are invited to the ceremony do not attend unless contacted
          directly.
        </p>

        <p>
          Our wedding reception has now been postponed. We will not be rebooking
          a specific date for the time being, but hope to be able to host a
          larger party with all of our guests later in the autumn or winter.
        </p>

